Collapse is a collaboration between ScanLab and New Movement Collective. Presented at Southbank Centre in 2016, the piece is the laser scan equivalent of long exposure photography, ScanLab call "Slow Life Scanning". 

The performance was accompanied by an "Exhibition of Remains", of 3D printed and Laser Cut sculptures. 

https://scanlabprojects.co.uk/work/collapse/
https://www.wired.co.uk/article/3d-scanning-dancing
